# Container virtualization

# Install and use in the [DigitalOcean Docker tutorial](https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-and-use-docker-on-ubuntu-18-04)

# **Image:** Files and config that can be instantiated.
# **Container:** Instantiation of an image. Can be run/stop/start...

# Basic docker:
docker search ubuntudocker pull ubuntu
# run or pull from Docker Hub and rundocker run hello-world

# Manage images
docker imagesdocker rmi [imageid]

# Run and get console:
docker run -it ubuntu

# Manage containers:
docker ps     # Show runnint containersdocker ps -a  # Show all (stopped inc.)
docker start [id|name]docker stop  [id|name]docker rm    [id|name]
